INSERT INTO `candidates` VALUES (21,'Jeff','Mataya','Carnegie Mellon University','Tepper School of Business','MBA','jeff.mataya@gmail.com',NULL,'First!',NULL),(22,'Daniel','Bishop','University of Pittsburgh','Medicine (pitt), CMU (BME)','the shit','hfhhg',NULL,'take over the world!',NULL),(24,'Anoopum','Gupta','Carnegie Mellon University','Robotics Institute','MD/PhD','anoopum@cmu.edu',NULL,'Interested in health technology.',NULL),(25,'Ashish','Parikh','University of Pittsburgh','Bionegineering','PhD','aap45@pitt.edu',NULL,'I will be graduating with my doctorate. There are ideas which I need to share with others and also learn about the industry.',NULL),(26,'Chris','Hobson','University of Pittsburgh','McGowan Institute for Regenerative Medicine','Ph.D','Chobson@gmail.com',NULL,'Interested in becoming better acquainted with the translation of IP or ideas from a university setting towards a clinical end point',NULL),(27,'Meenal','Patel','University of Pittsburgh','School of Bioengineering','Ph.D.','mjp101@pitt.edu',NULL,'I am very interested in gaining entrepreneurship skill and hopefully one day being a part of a healthcare related start-up. I think IACT is a wonderful opportunity to help me achieve my goals and learn about entrepreneurship first-hand.',NULL),(28,'Ryan','Bove','Carnegie Mellon University','Tepper School of Business','M.B.A.','ryanbove@tepper.cmu.edu',NULL,'I would like to support the development of entrepreneurship at Tepper and the Pittsburgh region.',NULL),(29,'Jing','Wang','University of Pittsburgh','School of Nursing','Postdoctoral','jiw38@pitt.edu',NULL,'I have been working on using smartphone and nationwide clinical information system for obesity and diabetes. My next step o research will involve development or implement using smartphone to connect with the clinical information system so that health care providers could access information on the web, provided by patients self-montoring using smartphones. I am also interested in working with companies to develop better apps in the smartphone for patient self-monitoring.',NULL),(30,'Daniel','Ludwig','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','M.D.','ludwig.daniel@medstudent.pitt.edu',NULL,'I\'ve always been very interested in the application of engineering solutions to improve the practice of medicine and decrease the cost of providing care. I was a biomedical engineering major from Brown University where I worked on the development of an electrochemical biosensor to reduce the time and cost associated with diagnosing vitamin D deficiency. I am currently in a 5 year research program (Physician Scientist Training Program) at UPSOM where I hope to use my engineering background together with my medical training to develop new devices and technology. I am currently working with a group of students at Pitt and CMU (Hygenyx Labs) on an initiative to improve hand hygiene compliance at UPMC. The Innovator\'s Challenge seems like an exciting opportunity to develop my interest in healthcare technology.',NULL),(31,'Yun','Jiang','University of Pittsburgh','School of Nursing','Ph.D.','yuj10@pitt.edu',NULL,'Majored in Nursing Informatics, expect to explore technology interventions to help older adults manage medicaiton regimen.',NULL),(32,'Kathleen','Hopkins','University of Pittsburgh','School of Nursing','pre-doctoral','kgh6@pitt.edu',NULL,'My proposed dissertation research will use ACCESS computer based instrument entry and be the first to comprehensively examine the symptom experience following surgical resection for early stage lung cancer, including the experience of patients with and without post thoracotomy pain syndrome (PTPS). Interventions targeted to improve postoperative recovery following surgery for lung cancer are limited and can be time-intensive in regard to resources and personnel, considerations that tend to limit translation into clinical practice. The purpose of this mixed-methods study is to document the symptom experience, influencing factors, and performance limitations of lung cancer patients during the first year after surgery, particularly patients with and without PTPS. Typically described as aching, burning, or extreme sensitivity to touch at or near the scar or chest tube insertion site, the etiology of PTPS is distinct from the side effects of cancer treatment or cancer progression. Eighty-four subjects will be recruited using convenience sampling and purposive selection from University of Pittsburgh Medical Center who are: 1) diagnosed with Stage 1 or 2 lung cancer without evidence of metatstasis, 2) managed surgically (no chemotherapy or radiotherapy), and 3) between 2 and 12 months post surgery. The applicantâ€™s long-term research goal is to use study findings, to design an interactive health communication application (IHCA) to improve symptom management for lung cancer patients. It is anticipated that the proposed IHCA will provide lung cancer patients with customizable, evidenced-based symptom management strategies. [IRB approval has been obtained for a pilot version of this study.]',NULL),(34,'Edan','Yago','Carnegie Mellon University','Tepper School of Buisness','Masters','yago@cmu.edu',NULL,'Currently involved in a start-up commercializing a novel from of cancer diagnostic. The technology was developed in CMU labs. Start-up is currently working on building and pitching the business plan.',NULL),(35,'Craig','Teegarden','Carnegie Mellon University','Electrical and Computer Engineering','Ph.D.','cteegard@ece.cmu.edu',NULL,'I am interested in developing new technology, especially technology that can help people -- medical technology is a perfect fit for interdisciplinary technology development.',NULL),(36,'Scott','Fisk','Carnegie Mellon University','Electrical and Computer Engineering','Ph.D','sfisk@andrew.cmu.edu',NULL,'I am interested in innovative healthcare technology. My current work as a PhD student is in the realm of wearable computing and virtual coaches. Virtual coaches are devices that offer constructive and relevant feedback to the user on the performance of a certain task. I believe there to be many applications of virtual coaches in healthcare. I am also part of Hygenyx Labs, a student led academic tech development group, currently looking into tech solutions for problems in the healthcare industry.',NULL),(37,'Pedro','Alvarez-Urena','Carnegie Mellon University','Biomedical Engineering','Masters','pedroa@andrew.cmu.edu',NULL,'Be able to know what to do with ideas, that can become innovations. How to get a concept from the clinic or bench, into the market-place? How to get the investment to get FDA approval?',NULL),(38,'Greggory','Housler','University of Pittsburgh','Bioengineering','Ph.D','houslergj@upmc.edu',NULL,'Collaboration.',NULL),(39,'Yujuan','Zhao','University of Pittsburgh','Bioengineering Department','PhD','yuz36@pitt.edu',NULL,'I would like to learn about healthcare technology opportunities from outside of school. This will help me to decide future options after graduation.',NULL),(40,'Don','Taylor','University of Pittsburgh','Bioengineering','Ph.D.','Dpt9@Pitt.edu',NULL,'To contribute, collaborate and compete',NULL),(41,'Avinash','Patil','University of Pittsburgh','Bioengineering','Ph.D.','ajp79@pitt.edu',NULL,'The reason I am interested in this workshop is, I am from India. In India I have seen many aging people are facing problems related to day to day activities e.g. restricted mobility, no communication channel, and lack of health care facilities. Overall, I think Indian society has failed to address those problems effectively.\r\nWith such workshop at least I can learn how to address those problems.',NULL),(42,'Jonathan','Raviotta','University of Pittsburgh','Behavioral and Community Health Sciences GSPH','MPH','jraviotta@gmail.com',NULL,'Technology has played a leading role in health care innovation since the dawn of time. New digital communication technology and the internet have finally opened the door to impacting the most complicated aspect of public health - human behavior. I am passionate about developing new ways to impact individuals\' health behavior using technology. I would welcome the challenge to create a device or implement a technological strategy to improve the public health. \r\n\r\nI am an avid technology enthusiast with a keen ability to bridge the device-human gap. Including me on a research team would add the requisite skills to insure usability, diffusion, acceptance, and growth of a selected technology. With a 15 year background in psychology and business management, my leadership and team facilitation skills will ensure the work group is effectively coordinated and accountable for delivery.\r\n\r\nThanks for considering my application.',NULL),(43,'Stefano','Gridelli','Carnegie Mellon University','Tepper School of Business','Masters','sgridell@tepper.cmu.edu',NULL,'Especially in the last decade we have seen how healthcare and computer science are always more bound together by technology improvement and integration of medical procedures delivered by Information Technology systems. As a network engineer working for the University of Pittsburgh Medical Center I realize every day how important is my job to deliver a world class healthcare to our patients. Also I believe that the current technologies adopted by the healthcare industry can be improved and that there\'s always room and need for new solutions and applications that aim to improve the activities of doctors and nurses to deliver the best care to patients. \r\nBy participating to this seminar I would bring my unique insights to the group and at the same time I would benefit myself because of the educational mini seminars that are included.',NULL),(44,'Test','','blank','','','',NULL,'',NULL),(45,'Jeevan','Pendli','Carnegie Mellon University','Tepper','MBA','jpendli@tepper.cmu.edu',NULL,'I want to contribute to the IAct idea.',NULL),(46,'John','Durkin','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','M.D.','john.r.durkin@gmail.com',NULL,'I am interested in using my engineering background and medical degree to develop medical software and tools.',NULL),(47,'Vamsi','Ambati','Carnegie Mellon University','LTI','Ph.D','vamshi@cmu.edu',NULL,'I want to understand the challenges in providing healthcare in developing nations',NULL),(48,'Bahar','Laderian','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','M.D.','baharladerian@gmail.com',NULL,'As an engineer, I have always been fascinated with science and technology. As a medical student, I am interested in improvement of healthcare and believe that medical advances are only possible with collaboration of scientists, physicians, and engineers in an interprofessional environment. The purpose of interdisciplinary projects is to brainstorm and formulate new methods and hi-tech inventions to treat patients more efficiently and accurately. IACT Innovator\'s Challenge is a great opportunity for me to combine two things that I am passionate about: healthcare and technology.',NULL),(49,'Mehwish','Nagda','Carnegie Mellon University','Human Computer Interaction','Masters','m.nagda@gmail.com',NULL,'- Learn more about the most pressing and important problems in the area, specifically related to Healthcare IT + software/hardware\r\n- Learn about strategies used in solving those problems\r\n- Connect with others interested in entrepreneurship',NULL),(50,'Hongwu','Wang','University of Pittsburgh','Rehabilitation Science','PhD','hwwang0301@gmail.com',NULL,'As a research student working at an interdisciplinary field, I am always interested in how to transfer the technology to commercialization. At same time, a workshop like this will provide me great opportunity to know people from different back ground but have similar interests.',NULL),(51,'Saleh','AlQahtani','University of Pittsburgh','Schoole of Health and Rehab Science','Master of Rehab Science and Technology','saa772@pitt.edu',NULL,'',NULL),(52,'Mark','Smiley','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine and Katz school of business','MD/MBA','smiley.mark@medstudent.pitt.edu',NULL,'I am a medical and business student interested in technologies and business opportunities that will change the way health care is delivered to an aging population.',NULL),(53,'Christine','LIN','Carnegie Mellon University','Heinz, Information Systems Management','Masters','cvl@andrew.cmu.edu',NULL,'I am interested in health care technology and would like the opportunity to gain more exposure and apply my ideas. I see this as a learning experience and a challenge that would be enriching.',NULL),(54,'Usha','Kuppuswamy','Carnegie Mellon University','Biomedical Engineering','PhD','ukuppusw@andrew.cmu.edu',NULL,'',NULL),(55,'Brendon','Philipps','Carnegie Mellon University','Tepper School of Business','MBA','Bphilipp@tepper.cmu.edu',NULL,'To learn more about healthcare technology an propel my entreprenierial ideas in the healthcare space and supplement my immediate career as a healthcare investment banker.',NULL),(56,'David','Randall','Carnegie Mellon University','Human-Computer Interaction','Masters','drandall@cmu.edu',NULL,'I worked for three years as a project manager at the medical software company Epic, where I got interested in software design and HCI. I am very interested in engaging with clinicians and others interested  in the field and re-entering the medical software industry once I\'m done at CMU.',NULL),(57,'Ee Kent','Lew','Carnegie Mellon University','Electrical and Computer Engineering','Bachelors','eekentl@andrew.cmu.edu',NULL,'To learn and gain experience.',NULL),(58,'Eric','Wu','Carnegie Mellon University','School of Computer Science','Undergrad','ericwu@andrew.cmu.edu',NULL,'I would like to attend IACT because I consider myself as a budding entrepreneur who wants to do good while making a fortune--technological innovations in health care would allow me to do just that. I have attended many events held by Project Olympus in the past few years but have not started a company yet because I have not found a suitable partner--an opportunity that IACT will provide. As my background is primarily in Computer Science, I am interested in meeting and developing relationships with fellow entrepreneurs that have a health care background from other top tier schools such as the University of Pittsburgh.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, as Carnegie Mellon\'s Student Body Vice President for Finance and a world traveler who has lived on four continents, I will also bring a global perspective and fiscal responsibility to a startup.',NULL),(59,'James','Chun','Carnegie Mellon University','Carnegie Institute of Technology','Bsc','jtchun@andrew.cmu.edu',NULL,'I have always been fascinated with technology, and its huge potential for growth and improving the quality of our lives. While I enjoy working through the technical details of problems, I have always known that the full potential of technology can only be unlocked through the use of business and financing. To pursue my passion, I enrolled in Carnegie Mellon University, and am double majoring in Electrical and Computer Engineering and Economics. I believe that the Innovator\'s Challenge will allow me to further explore my interests. It will not only give me insight into how innovation and entrepreneurship are born, but will also give me the opportunity to interact with like-minded people. I am very excited to attend these talks and develop ideas, and sincerely hope that I will be able to attend the Innovator\'s Challenge.',NULL),(60,'W. Ben','Towne','Carnegie Mellon University','Computation, Organizations, &amp; Society (SCS)','PhD','wbt+iact@cs.cmu.edu',NULL,'I am active in the area of building sociotechnical ecosystems for health information technology.  For a sample of recent work, see &quot;The VistA Ecosystem: Current Status and Future Directions,&quot; http://conway.isri.cmu.edu/%7Ejdh/web-pubs/pdfs/vista_report_2010_final-formatted.pdf .  My focus is on ways to bring in perspectives from people in industry, academica, clinics, etc. to help Inform The Debate about policy decisions (and technical decisions with policy implications) in a complex system such as this open-source electronic health records application suite.  \r\nNote: I am unsure regarding travel plans for 1/22 and do not know 100% if I can make this event or not.  I\'d like to come, but if you need near certainty, I don\'t have that information yet.  Thanks for organizing the conference!',NULL),(61,'Wei','Wei','Carnegie Mellon University','School of computer science','Phd','Weiwei@cs.cmu.edu',NULL,'Have a bunch of technologies that can be applied to health care industrial.',NULL),(62,'Peter','Rodgers-Fischl','Carnegie Mellon University','Biomedical Engineering','Masters','prfischl@gmail.com',NULL,'I wish to become an entrepeneur.  This means that I must not only learn how to create project proposals (or even elevator proposals), but also network.',NULL),(63,'Yvonne','Weideman','blank','School of Nursing','DNP graduate','weidemany@duq.edu',NULL,'I am one of this years Jone of Salk Fellows and I am applying to the challange via an invitation to all of the Salk Fellows.  I am a recent Doctor of Nursing Practice (DNP) graduate and am currently working as faculty at a local school of nursing in a community based program. I have a special interest in health technology and innovations that assit the elderly in learning to manage chronic diseases and to live at home independently. My past experiences includes consulting with developers on a home monitoring device for early discharge after bone marrow transplants and a computerized phone triage system for home infusion companies. More recently I developed a virtual learning model, patent pending, for students to facilitate learning about the health promotion needs of the woman with a healthy pregnancy and the needs of the developing fetus.  It is my hope that this model for learning can eventually be adpated to facilitate patient education for caregivers/aging patients iving with various chronic illnesses.  \r\n\r\nI think that my background and experience as a Nurses in the community setting will enable me to bring a unique perspective to the Challenge and I look forward to meeting and working with people from other industries on healthcare technology innovations through the Innovator\'s Challenge.',NULL),(64,'Portia','Taylor','Carnegie Mellon University','Biomedical Engineering','PhD','pet@andrew.cmu.edu',NULL,'I currently work in the area of developing intelligent systems for at-home therapeutic exercise.  I am designing and developing a system that could impact healthcare by allowing people to get proper rehabilitative exercises at home with a focus on the quality of motions performed by the patient.  Our goal is to provide a low-cost platform for encouraging adherence to home exercises to increase joint mobility after a disease or injury.\r\n\r\nIt is my goal to see my system in the hands of the end user.  At the conclusion of my thesis work, I intend on pursuing possible business and tech transfer opportunities.  Attending the IACT Innovators Challenge will give me the opportunity to learn what it takes for an idea to go to market and the necessary steps needed in order to start on that path.  \r\n\r\nAs I am a 4th year PhD student looking to graduate May 2012, I am very motivated to learn about opportunities that may be available to me upon graduation.  Please consider my application to your challenge.  I have a lot of great ideas and work well with others.  The experience will be another step in shaping my future career.',NULL),(68,'Jeff','Mataya','Carnegie Mellon University','Tepper School of Business','MBA','jmataya@tepper.cmu.edu',NULL,'Website Test',NULL),(69,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL),(70,'Andrew','Phelps','Carnegie Mellon University','Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering','Ph.D.','raphelps@cmu.edu',NULL,'I found out about this through a friend and I am interested in healthcare technology and start-ups.',NULL),(71,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL),(72,'Sayali','Kadam','Carnegie Mellon University','Heinz College','MS Biotechnology and Management','skadam@andrew.cmu.edu',NULL,'This year\'s IACT Innovator\'s Challenge is about collaborating and creating an innovative concept for healthcare technologies for an aging America. This challenge provides an exciting opportunity to bring my experiences from the Biotechnology area to the table and collaborate and network with other students/professionals to introduce a new concept. I would greatly value this opportunity to attend the Innovator\'s Challenge.',NULL),(73,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL),(74,'Han','Wang','Carnegie Mellon University','Healthcare policy and management','Masters','hanw1@andrew.cmu.edu',NULL,'I want to interact with physicians and industries to know the real world problems that need to be addressed and work with multiplinary teams to address those problems.',NULL),(75,'Kawa','Shwaish','University of Pittsburgh','Katz School of Business','MBA / MS MIS','kawash@gmail.com',NULL,'I am interested in the offered workshops and in connecting with like minded students with an entrepreneurship drive. \r\n\r\nI am looking to drive some of my seed projects and find other to collaborate with.',NULL),(76,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL),(77,'Madhur','Gupta','University of Pittsburgh','Katz Graduate School of Business','Masters','mag181@pitt.edu',NULL,'I am passionate about knowing new technologies and how these technologies can support businesses to provide better services, products and value to their customers. \r\nInnovator\'s Challenge event will help me in understanding the current problems and needs of health-care industry and how technology can meet those needs and solve critical business problems. \r\nI will learn about the latest technology trends in the health-care industry and will utilize my knowledge and experience in the IT industry to find best possible solutions for some of the persistent problems in the industry.\r\nThis event will also provide me opportunity to meet people from different domains and to learn from their knowledge and experience.',NULL),(78,'Mayank','Mamtani','Carnegie Mellon University','Heinz College','MS Biotechnology Management','mayank.mamtani@gmail.com',NULL,'I want to pursue a career in healthcare and biotechnology and hence I believe that this would be an ideal platform for me to gain some key insights on the industry and add on to my learning in the grad experience at Carnegie Mellon. Besides, I have a few ideas to contribute to the healthcare, more so on the provider side and hence believe for it to be a good opportunity to build on to that and formulate some strategies to carry it forward.',NULL),(79,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL),(80,'Karleen','Leveille','University of Pittsburgh','Katz School of Business','Masters','kal106@pitt.edu',NULL,'I have a business that is getting ready to launch a product that will involve others in the medical and health field.',NULL),(81,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL),(82,'Arif','Rashid','University of Pittsburgh','SOM','M.D.','rsarif@seas.upenn.edu',NULL,'I have been involved in learning about research and innovation since my time at Penn where I was a dual-degree student in economics and bioengineering. I have taken a number of courses of in entrepreneurship and product design and have a keen sense of how opportunities are identified and explored. Complementing that I have been involved in engineering research, focusing on radiology/molecular imaging, for the past 2 years, and equally am developing a good understanding of how theoretical knowledge is developed and the sorts of paths it takes towards becoming actionable technologies. Lastly, I have had experience in different setting in interdisciplinary team environments, to the sort environment which is crucial in order to properly foster an idea/concept to reality.\r\n\r\nWill leave it at that, if you would like more information, please do not hesistate to email me.\r\n\r\nI am quite excited about the sort of activities IACT is trying to inspire and I am very impressed with the depth of thought that has gone into the model. Most of all I would like to meet and work with similarly minded individual accross CMU and Pitt.\r\n\r\nArif',NULL),(83,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL);
