INSERT INTO `candidates_surgical` VALUES (25,'Avinash','Patil','University of Pittsburgh','Bioengineering','Ph.D.','ajp79@pitt.edu',NULL,'I am interested to participate in Surgical Innovation workshop to learn from surgeon\'s perspective and use my Engineering background to solve challenging medical problems.',NULL,0),(26,'Sudhir','Pathak','University of Pittsburgh','Bioengineering','PhD','skpathak@pitt.edu',NULL,'My area of research involved Damage accessment in Neurosurgery. I am working on Diffusion Weighted MRI to create fibers tracks which can be helpful in Presurgical Planning. For details see &quot;High-definition fiber tracking guidance for intraparenchymal endoscopic port surgery.&quot; in J Neurosurg. 2010 Nov;113(5):990-9. Epub 2009 Nov 27.\r\n \r\nI wanted to attend this event to expand my research with current novel technology. I think this is great opportunity to know upcoming surgical technology.',NULL,0),(27,'Ashish','Parikh','University of Pittsburgh','Bionegineering','','aap45@pitt.edu',NULL,'Networking and learn about the state of the art    surgical innovations and apply it to my research',NULL,0),(28,'Kalidasan','Thambiayya','University of Pittsburgh','Bioengineering','Ph.D','thk25@pitt.edu',NULL,'Would want to create contact with researchers and business leaders.',NULL,0),(29,'Mark','Langhans','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','M.D./Ph.D','langhans.mark@medstudent.pitt.edu',NULL,'I study developmental biology with the goal of applying it to surgical innovation.  I want to learn about opportunities for innovation.',NULL,0),(30,'Matthew','Pigott','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','MD','pigott.matthew@medstudent.pitt.edu',NULL,'I plan on pursuing a career in Orthopaedic Surgery and would like to have a hand in developing new technologies to improve surgical outcomes.  I hope to learn more about the process of turning ideas into innovations and about what type of people need to be involved in that process.  I have extensive experience shadowing physicians from multiple surgical specialties in the OR, which I feel will allow me to add a perspective on the common challenges faced.',NULL,0),(31,'Test','Test','Carnegie Mellon University','Test','Test','Test',NULL,'Test',NULL,0),(32,'Jeff','Mataya','Carnegie Mellon University','Tepper School of Business','MBA','jmataya@tepper.cmu.edu',NULL,'I\'m Rick James, bitch.',NULL,0),(33,'Kwesi','St. Louis','blank','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(34,'Kwesi','St. Louis','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','M.D','st.louis.kwesi@medstudent.pitt.edu',NULL,'I want to get involved with IACT and this seems like the best way to do it.',NULL,0),(35,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(36,'Umar','Salimi','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','M.D.','salimi.umar@medstudent.pitt.edu',NULL,'I would like to go into surgery and familiarize myself not only with recent innovations but the process of developing surgical technology.',NULL,0),(37,'Nicholas','Amoroso','University of Pittsburgh','Bioengineering','Ph.D.','nicholas.amoroso@gmail.com',NULL,'I am beginning my final year of my Ph.D. research here at the University of Pittsburgh, and I am eager to meet with potential collaborators, or even employers.  My dissertation focuses on the development and utilization of elastomeric electrospun constructs for cardiovascular applications.  As such, I am very interested in surgical research.  I am excited for the opportunity to meet and discuss with researchers that my offer new insights into my own work.  I also feel that I would be able to contribute my personal experience and knowledge of the literature to discussions.  I am always pleased when I am able to talk with clinicians about their needs, and how they may be met through an engineered design. I do not often, however, have the opportunity to discuss these topics with business leaders, and am particularly excited to do so.\r\n\r\nThank you for your consideration.\r\n\r\n-Nicholas Amoroso',NULL,0),(38,'Bahar','Laderian','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','M.D.','baharladerian@gmail.com',NULL,'As an engineer and medical student, I would like to be involved in such a great workshop. I always wanted to participate in a technology-driven workshop/group that focuses on enhancing medical equipment to improve hospitals\' aptitude in treating patients. I sincerely hope to be a part of this workshop.',NULL,0),(39,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(40,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(41,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(42,'John','Durkin','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','M.D.','john.r.durkin@gmail.com',NULL,'I enjoyed the previous IACT event, and I am interested in starting a business related to medicine.',NULL,0),(43,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(44,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(45,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(46,'Satish','Singh','University of Pittsburgh','Chemical Engineering','Ph.D.','sss42@pitt.edu',NULL,'As a third year Ph.D. student working on the development and application of synthetic bone graft substitutes, I have realized that an integral part of biomedical research is communicating efficiently with and understanding the problems faced daily by clinicians. Only when these problems are fully understood by researchers is when suitable engineering principles can be applied to solve them. I believe the IACT workshop provides an ideal forum for facilitating such communication between not only clinicians and academic researchers, but also industry. Gaining valuable industrial work experience is one my future career goals, particularly with respect to technology transfer and commercialization. Unfortunately, at this point I believe one of my weaknesses is not having as much knowledge about intellectual property and the patent process. Attending the IACT workshop would provide an excellent opportunity to not only network with people from various backgrounds and disciplines, but may potentially provide a means to find out more about resources that are available to graduate students to assist in educating them on technology transfer and commercialization, such as venture mentoring programs. As a member of the student leadership council for a generation 3 NSF funded Engineering Research Center (ERC), this workshop is also of interest to me as a potential way of getting the students of our ERC more involved with the community and enhancing the awareness of our centerâ€™s goal which is to revolutionize metallic biomaterials.',NULL,0),(47,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(48,'Arif','Rashid','University of Pittsburgh','SOM','MD','rsarif@seas.upenn.edu',NULL,'Can you please see the email I sent in for the innovators challenge, which I sent by mistake to that page by mistaske.\r\n\r\nARif',NULL,0),(49,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(50,'Arif','Rashid','University of Pittsburgh','SOM','MD','rsarif@seas.upenn.edu',NULL,'I have been involved in learning about research and innovation since\r\nmy time at Penn where I was a dual-degree student in economics and\r\nbioengineering. I have taken a number of courses of in\r\nentrepreneurship and product design and have a keen sense of how\r\nopportunities are identified and explored. Complementing that I have\r\nbeen involved in engineering research, focusing on radiology/molecular\r\nimaging, for the past 2 years, and equally am developing a good\r\nunderstanding of how theoretical knowledge is developed and the sorts\r\nof paths it takes towards becoming actionable technologies. Lastly, I\r\nhave had experience in different setting in interdisciplinary team\r\nenvironments, to the sort environment which is crucial in order to\r\nproperly foster an idea/concept to reality. Will leave it at that, if\r\nyou would like more information, please do not hesistate to email me.\r\nI am quite excited about the sort of activities IACT is trying to\r\ninspire and I am very impressed with the depth of thought that has\r\ngone into the model. Most of all I would like to meet and work with\r\nsimilarly minded individual accross CMU and Pitt. Arif',NULL,0),(51,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(52,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(53,'Nadeem','Kolia','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','M.D.','kolia.nadeem@medstudent.pitt.edu',NULL,'As an undergrad at Duke University I was a Biomedical Engineering and Electrical and Computer Engineering dual major. I am interested in specializing in surgery and both now as a medical student and in the future as a practicing surgeon I hope to use my training and skills in engineering to develop and prototype new surgical devices and procedures which can advance or even revolutionize the field. I\'m really excited for this workshop and I\'m glad that you guys have having such an event.',NULL,0),(54,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(55,'William','Denq','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','M.D.','denq.william@medstudent.pitt.edu',NULL,'This appears to be a fantastic opportunity to glimpse the direction and future of surgery, a field that I definitely want to have a profession in. Also it sounds like a good place to connect with professionals and other students in related fields.\r\n\r\n...pretty much sounds awesome.\r\n\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n-Will',NULL,0),(56,'Isaac','James','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','M.D.','james.isaac@medstudent.pitt.edu',NULL,'This sounds like an amazing experience to see future surgical innovation and network with people in the field. As a medical student who is planning to pursue a career in surgery, I would love the opportunity to attend.\r\n\r\n-Isaac James',NULL,0),(57,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(58,'John','Kang','Carnegie Mellon University','School of Computer Science','MD, PhD','kangjohn@cmu.edu',NULL,'I\'m interested in and have ideas about emerging surgery technology.',NULL,0),(59,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(60,'Marcher','Thompson','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','M.D.  MSII','thompson.marcher@medstudent.pitt.edu',NULL,'I am interested in medical technology and I would like to be a part of future technological advancements in the medical field.   I see this event as an opportunity for me to gain more information and knowledge about what I can do to become involved.  The announced speakers and topics look very interesting and I would love the opportunity to hear what they have to say.  As a future physician, I think that it is important to use my medical knowledge and the benefits technology can afford the field to best treat my future patients.',NULL,0),(61,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(62,'Chuck','Norris','University of Pittsburgh','Oral Maxillofacial Surgery','OMF Surgeon','moonlighter@gmail.com',NULL,'What is the point of this application to attend the event? Is Thomas Starzl going to be there? I mean come onnnnnnnnnnn.',NULL,0),(63,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(64,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(65,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(66,'Paul','Johnson','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','M.D.','pjohnsonj@gmail.com',NULL,'I have an active interest in developing surgical devices and medical equipment in general.',NULL,0),(67,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(68,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(69,'Elizabeth','Lee','University of Pittsburgh','Medicine','MD','lee.elizabeth@medstudent.pitt.edu',NULL,'I\'d like to learn more about how surgery can be changed in the future and where the field is currently heading.  I hope to come away from the event with ideas I can enact in combination with my interests in patient safety and quality improvement.',NULL,0),(70,'Sylekhya','Muddana','University of Pittsburgh','Business','Masters','sym6@pitt.edu',NULL,'It is my belief that this program offers an exciting platform for professionals with medical and business backgrounds to interact, this interaction could lead to groundbreaking products or processes. The importance of surgical innovation in today\'s world is invaluable. Being a business student I would be able to contribute to the underlying factors contributing to the sustainability and success of such innovations namely, financial structuring the process for feasibility as well as marketing measures to make aware the existence of such products. And last but not least the process control, to ensure that the product is available to those who are need. Coming from a medical family as well as a developing country I have a strong emotional connection to this field and thus I am in a position to contribute to certain aspects of the program that may lead to the inch of difference between success and failure.',NULL,0),(71,'Avinash','Patil','University of Pittsburgh','Bioengineering','Ph.D.','ajp79@pitt.edu',NULL,'Interested to learn medical technology',NULL,0),(72,'Kristen','Wolff','Duke University','School of Law','J.D.','wolffkri@gmail.com','248.943.6154','Interested in innovation in healthcare and cross-discipline collaboration.',NULL,0),(73,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(74,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(75,'Andrea','Shoffstall','University of Pittsburgh','Engineering','Undergrad','als178@pitt.edu',NULL,'I work for Cohera Medical, so I am very interested in learning more about Surgical Innovation.',NULL,0),(76,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(77,'Shang-Hsien','Chuang','University of Pittsburgh','Katz Graduate school of Business','Master','shc64@pitt.edu',NULL,'I would like to pursue my post MBA career in health care industry, so gaining more information and knowledge about it will be helpful.',NULL,0),(78,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(79,'Mithun','Neral','University of Pittsburgh','School of Medicine','M.D.','neral.mithun@medstudent.pitt.edu',NULL,'Cuz IACT is the shit',NULL,0),(80,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(81,'','','','','','',NULL,'',NULL,0),(82,'Adam','Simone','Carnegie Mellon University','Biotechnology and Management','Masters','asimone@andrew.cmu.edu',NULL,'makin it happen',NULL,0),(83,'Jonathan','Raviotta','Univers